-- в”Ђв”Ђ MailerLite в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$MailerLite is an email marketing and automation platform aimed at small businesses and creators, offering campaigns, automation, landing pages, and websites in one tool.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (paid plans from $12/month)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2010, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Vilnius, Lithuania$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$MailerLite Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$MailerLite review covering email marketing features, 2026 pricing changes, automation and landing page tools, pros and cons, and top alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$MailerLite is an email marketing and marketing automation platform founded in 2010 by Ignas Rubezius in Vilnius, Lithuania, initially as a side project before growing into a bootstrapped, fully distributed company serving well over a million users across more than 130 countries. In April 2022, MailerLite was acquired by Vercom, a Polish communications technology group, though it has continued to operate under the MailerLite brand. The platform is built around a simple, design-forward email builder combined with automation workflows, landing pages, websites, signup forms, and lightweight e-commerce and digital product/booking tools, positioning it as an accessible alternative to more complex platforms like Mailchimp or HubSpot. Its editor offers three modes, drag-and-drop, custom HTML, and a simplified rich-text editor, and the platform includes an AI writing assistant, dynamic content personalization, and a subscriber preference center. MailerLite made a significant pricing and plan restructuring in mid-2026, renaming its Growing Business and Advanced tiers to Comfort and Power and raising prices across most subscriber tiers by roughly 10 to 30 percent. As of the current structure, the free plan covers up to 250 active subscribers with 2,500 monthly emails and two user seats; the Comfort plan starts at 12 dollars per month for 500 subscribers and scales monthly sending allowance to roughly ten times the subscriber ceiling, while adding automations, multiple websites and landing pages, and digital product/booking support; the Power plan starts at 25 dollars per month and unlocks unlimited monthly emails, unlimited user seats and automations, and 24/7 live chat support; and an Enterprise tier with custom pricing is available for accounts above 200,000 subscribers, including a dedicated success manager and deliverability support. MailerLite's target audience is solo creators, bloggers, small e-commerce stores, and small-to-midsize businesses that want strong design and ease of use without the cost and complexity of larger marketing suites. Its main competitors include Mailchimp, Brevo, ActiveCampaign, ConvertKit (Kit), and Constant Contact. MailerLite differentiates itself primarily through its clean, minimalist editor, historically lower pricing than Mailchimp for comparable list sizes (though the 2026 repricing narrowed that gap), and a bundled website/landing-page builder that lets small businesses run a full web presence and email program from one platform.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'eb14d50a-e3a5-457e-8b21-c45cdda89d54';

